<box>
\begin{equation*}
\text{{Average}} = \frac{\sum_{i=1}^{n} X_i}{n}
\end{equation*}

where $X_i$ represents the age of each turtle and $n$ is the total number of turtles. In this case, we have four Ninja Turtles with ages 15, 15, 17, and 17 years old. So, we can calculate their average age as:

<box>
\begin{equation*}
\text{{Average Age}} = \frac{(15+15+17+17)}{4} = \boxed{\textbf{16 years old}}
\end{equation*}
</box>

So, the average age of the Ninja Turtles is 16 years old.

